          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-4931 ladvise: Add feature of giving file access advices",
        "message": "LU-4931 ladvise: Add feature of giving file access advices\n\nLinux kernel provide mechanism to applications to give advices\nor hints about how to choose appropriate read-ahead and caching\ntechniques to the corresponding file. However, this is only a\nclient side mechanism which is not enough for distributed file\nsystems like Lustre, because in order to tune the system-wide\ncache or read-ahead policies, server needs to understand the\nadvices too.\n\nThis patch adds a new feature which provides new APIs and utils\nto give advices about the access pattern of Lustre file with the\npurpose of performance improvement. It can pass advices directly\nthrough Lustre client to server/storage side.\n\nSigned-off-by: Li Xi <lixi@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I42a91a9d042cc082e54acab19e1904421bf89580\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
